# Role Dynamic Preload Complete Flow:

01. User Add/Update page open karta hai:
    URL → UserCtl

02. Request UserCtl par jati hai aur BaseCtl ki service() method call hoti hai.

03. service() method me sabse pehle preload(request) method call hoti hai.

04. preload() method UserCtl me override hoti hai.

05. preload() method me RoleModel ka object banaya jata hai:
    RoleModel roleModel = new RoleModel();

06. roleModel.list() method call hoti hai:
    - ye database se saare roles fetch karti hai

07. list() method internally search(null, 0, 0) call karti hai.

08. RoleModel.search() method me SQL query banti hai:
    select * from st_role where 1=1

09. Query execute hoti hai aur database se sab Role records fetch hote hain.

10. Har record ko RoleBean object me map kiya jata hai:
    - id set hota hai
    - name set hota hai
    - description set hota hai

11. Saare RoleBean objects ko List me add kiya jata hai.

12. Ye List<RoleBean> preload() method ko return hoti hai.

13. preload() method me:
    request.setAttribute("roleList", roleList) set kiya jata hai.

14. JSP me:
    List roleList = (List) request.getAttribute("roleList") se list get hoti hai.

15. HTMLUtility.getList("roleId", selectedValue, roleList) method call hoti hai.

16. HTMLUtility.getList() method me:
    - StringBuffer se <select> tag create hota hai
    - default option add hota hai

22. Loop chalaya jata hai:
    for (DropdownListBean obj : roleList)

17. Har RoleBean ke liye:
    - key = obj.getKey() → id
    - value = obj.getValue() → role name

18. Har role ke liye option tag banaya jata hai:
    <option value='id'>role name</option>

19. Agar koi value selected hai to:
    us option me "selected" attribute add hota hai

20. Loop complete hone ke baad:
    </select> close kiya jata hai

21. Final dropdown HTML string return hoti hai.

28. JSP me ye HTML render hoti hai.

29. Final output:
    Role dropdown dynamically database se load ho kar user form me display hota hai.
